authentication and authorization as a plug-in.

00:35:11.489 --> 00:35:12.919
What does that mean?

00:35:12.920 --> 00:35:19.590
That means it's possible for you guys to go out and create
your own authentication and authorization mechanism based

00:35:19.590 --> 00:35:26.260
on something like Shibboleth, OpenID, whatever
it is that you happen to be working with.

00:35:26.260 --> 00:35:30.790
I am going to take a quick aside and talk
about authentication versus authorization.

00:35:30.789 --> 00:35:33.710
Authentication is you are who you say who you are.

00:35:33.710 --> 00:35:37.470
Authorization is you can do what
it is that you're trying to do.

00:35:37.469 --> 00:35:43.099
I bring it up because for something like Shibboleth, it's
pretty simple, it does authentication and authorization.

00:35:43.099 --> 00:35:45.750
For something like OpenID it only does authentication.

00:35:45.750 --> 00:35:51.280
So you're gonna have to figure out a way to do your own
authorization mapping underneath all of that.

00:35:51.280 --> 00:35:53.960
It's implemented as a twisted plug-in.

00:35:53.960 --> 00:35:58.809
